sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Client
    participant GW as API Gateway
    participant TR as Transfer Service
    participant LG as Ledger Service (workflow + activities)
    participant DDB as DynamoDB (balance + ledger — money truth)
    participant PG as PostgreSQL (metadata + balance cache)
    participant MQ as Event Bus (Kafka)
    participant TS as Temporal Service
    participant F as Fraud Engine
    participant X as ML / AML APIs (external)
    participant N as Notification

    rect rgb(225, 240, 255)
    Note over C,MQ: SYNCHRONOUS — Transfer calls Ledger to hold, fires event, returns accepted + balance
    C->>GW: POST /v1/transfers (Idempotency-Key, JWT)
    GW->>GW: JWT verify / rate limit
    GW->>TR: createTransfer(req)
    TR->>TR: daily/per-txn limit check ($500 / $2,500)
    TR->>LG: hold(sender, recipient, amount, idempotency_key)
    LG->>PG: write transfers meta (status=DEBITED, amount, idempotency_key)
    alt key exists (duplicate)
        PG-->>LG: conflict → stored response
        LG-->>TR: existing result
        TR-->>C: 200 (same as before)
    else new request
        Note over LG,DDB: reserve funds — conditional UpdateItem (no ledger entry, no escrow)
        LG->>DDB: sender balance: held += amount, version += 1<br/>cond: available - held >= amount (else 422 insufficient)
        DDB-->>LG: OK (available unchanged — real money not moved yet)
        LG-->>TR: accepted (transfer_id, new available/held)
        TR->>MQ: fire TransferRequested
        TR-->>C: 200 OK (transfer_id, status=DEBITED, balance)
    end
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 225)
    Note over DDB,PG: DynamoDB Streams → refresh PostgreSQL balance cache (async, display only)
    DDB-->>PG: stream balance change → update balance_cache_minor
    end

    rect rgb(237, 231, 246)
    Note over MQ,N: ASYNC — Ledger Service runs the Temporal workflow itself (durable: state, timers, retries)
    MQ-->>LG: TransferRequested (consumed by Ledger)
    LG->>TS: StartWorkflow SettlementWorkflow(transfer_id)
    Note over LG,F: (1) fraud Activity (auto-retry, timeout)
    LG->>F: fraud / AML check
    F->>X: AML screening (+ ML scoring)
    X-->>F: result
    F-->>LG: ALLOW / REVIEW / DENY
    alt DENY  (or cancel Signal during moratorium)
        Note over LG,DDB: release the hold — no money ever moved (local Activity)
        LG->>DDB: sender balance: held -= amount (+ version bump)
        LG->>PG: transfers.status = CANCELLED
    else ALLOW
        Note over LG,TS: (2) moratorium = workflow.Sleep(settle_after) — DURABLE TIMER<br/>cancel Signal interrupts the timer → releaseHold
        LG->>TS: start durable timer until settle_after
        TS-->>LG: timer fired (settle_after reached)
        Note over LG,DDB: (3) settle Activity — local to Ledger (one TransactWriteItems, optimistic lock)
        LG->>DDB: read sender & recipient balance → versions Vs, Vr
        LG->>DDB: Update sender: available-=amt, held-=amt, version=Vs+1 (cond version=Vs)
        LG->>DDB: Update recipient: available+=amt, version=Vr+1 (cond version=Vr)
        LG->>DDB: Put DEBIT + CREDIT ledger entries (cond: idempotency_key not settled)
        DDB-->>LG: OK (or TransactionCanceledException → activity retries)
        LG->>PG: transfers.status = SETTLED
        Note over LG,N: (4) notify Activity
        LG->>MQ: publish TransferSettled
        MQ-->>N: notify sender & recipient (Push/SMS/Email)
    end
    end
